380.dex: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

381.name: Latios
381.dex: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

382.name: Kyogre
382.dex: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

383.name: Groudon
383.dex: Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can cause magma to erupt and expand the landmass of the world.

384.name: Rayquaza
384.dex: It flies forever through the ozone layer, consuming meteoroids for sustenance. The many meteoroids in its body provide the energy it needs to Mega Evolve.

385.name: Jirachi
385.dex: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

386.name: Deoxys
386.dex: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon's chest appears to be its brain.

387.name: Turtwig
387.dex: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

388.name: Grotle
388.dex: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

389.name: Torterra
389.dex: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

390.name: Chimchar
390.dex: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

391.name: Monferno
391.dex: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

392.name: Infernape
392.dex: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

393.name: Piplup
393.dex: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

394.name: Prinplup
394.dex: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

395.name: Empoleon
395.dex: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

396.name: Starly
396.dex: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

397.name: Staravia
397.dex: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

398.name: Staraptor
398.dex: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

399.name: Bidoof
399.dex: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

400.name: Bibarel
400.dex: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

401.name: Kricketot
401.dex: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

402.name: Kricketune
402.dex: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

403.name: Shinx
403.dex: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

404.name: Luxio
404.dex: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

405.name: Luxray
405.dex: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

406.name: Budew
406.dex: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

407.name: Roserade
407.dex: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

408.name: Cranidos
408.dex: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

409.name: Rampardos
409.dex: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

410.name: Shieldon
410.dex: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

411.name: Bastiodon
411.dex: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

412.name: Burmy
412.dex: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

413.name: Wormadam
413.dex: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

414.name: Mothim
414.dex: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

415.name: Combee
415.dex: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

416.name: Vespiquen
416.dex: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

417.name: Pachirisu
417.dex: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

418.name: Buizel
418.dex: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

419.name: Floatzel
419.dex: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

420.name: Cherubi
420.dex: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

421.name: Cherrim
421.dex: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

422.name: Shellos
422.dex: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

423.name: Gastrodon
423.dex: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

424.name: Ambipom
424.dex: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

425.name: Drifloon
425.dex: These Pokémon are called the “Signpost for Wandering Spirits.” Children holding them sometimes vanish.

426.name: Drifblim
426.dex: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

427.name: Buneary
427.dex: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

428.name: Lopunny
428.dex: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

429.name: Mismagius
429.dex: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

430.name: Honchkrow
430.dex: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

431.name: Glameow
431.dex: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

432.name: Purugly
432.dex: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

433.name: Chingling
433.dex: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

434.name: Stunky
434.dex: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

435.name: Skuntank
435.dex: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

436.name: Bronzor
436.dex: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

437.name: Bronzong
437.dex: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

438.name: Bonsly
438.dex: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

439.name: Mime Jr.
439.dex: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

440.name: Happiny
440.dex: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

441.name: Chatot
441.dex: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

442.name: Spiritomb
442.dex: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

443.name: Gible
443.dex: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

444.name: Gabite
444.dex: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

445.name: Garchomp
445.dex: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

446.name: Munchlax
446.dex: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

447.name: Riolu
447.dex: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

448.name: Lucario
448.dex: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

449.name: Hippopotas
449.dex: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

450.name: Hippowdon
450.dex: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

451.name: Skorupi
451.dex: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

452.name: Drapion
452.dex: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

453.name: Croagunk
453.dex: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

454.name: Toxicroak
454.dex: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

455.name: Carnivine
455.dex: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

456.name: Finneon
456.dex: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

457.name: Lumineon
457.dex: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

458.name: Mantyke
458.dex: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

459.name: Snover
459.dex: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

460.name: Abomasnow
460.dex: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

461.name: Weavile
461.dex: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

462.name: Magnezone
462.dex: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

463.name: Lickilicky
463.dex: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

464.name: Rhyperior
464.dex: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

465.name: Tangrowth
465.dex: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

466.name: Electivire
466.dex: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

467.name: Magmortar
467.dex: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

468.name: Togekiss
468.dex: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

469.name: Yanmega
469.dex: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

470.name: Leafeon
470.dex: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

471.name: Glaceon
471.dex: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

472.name: Gliscor
472.dex: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

473.name: Mamoswine
473.dex: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

474.name: Porygon z
474.dex: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

475.name: Gallade
475.dex: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

476.name: Probopass
476.dex: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

477.name: Dusknoir
477.dex: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

478.name: Froslass
478.dex: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

479.name: Rotom
479.dex: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

480.name: Uxie
480.dex: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

481.name: Mesprit
481.dex: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

482.name: Azelf
482.dex: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

483.name: Dialga
483.dex: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

484.name: Palkia
484.dex: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

485.name: Heatran
485.dex: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

486.name: Regigigas
486.dex: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

487.name: Giratina
487.dex: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

488.name: Cresselia
488.dex: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

489.name: Phione
489.dex: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

490.name: Manaphy
490.dex: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

491.name: Darkrai
491.dex: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

492.name: Shaymin
492.dex: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

493.name: Arceus
493.dex: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

494.name: Victini
494.dex: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

495.name: Snivy
495.dex: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

496.name: Servine
496.dex: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

497.name: Serperior
497.dex: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

498.name: Tepig
498.dex: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

499.name: Pignite
499.dex: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

500.name: Emboar
500.dex: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

501.name: Oshawott
501.dex: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

502.name: Dewott
502.dex: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

503.name: Samurott
503.dex: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

504.name: Patrat
504.dex: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

505.name: Watchog
505.dex: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

506.name: Lillipup
506.dex: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

507.name: Herdier
507.dex: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

508.name: Stoutland
508.dex: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

509.name: Purrloin
509.dex: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

510.name: Liepard
510.dex: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

511.name: Pansage
511.dex: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

512.name: Simisage
512.dex: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

513.name: Pansear
513.dex: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

514.name: Simisear
514.dex: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

515.name: Panpour
515.dex: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

516.name: Simipour
516.dex: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

517.name: Munna
517.dex: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

518.name: Musharna
518.dex: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

519.name: Pidove
519.dex: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

520.name: Tranquill
520.dex: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

521.name: Unfezant
521.dex: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

522.name: Blitzle
522.dex: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

523.name: Zebstrika
523.dex: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

524.name: Roggenrola
524.dex: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

525.name: Boldore
525.dex: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

526.name: Gigalith
526.dex: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

527.name: Woobat
527.dex: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

528.name: Swoobat
528.dex: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

529.name: Drilbur
529.dex: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

530.name: Excadrill
530.dex: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

531.name: Audino
531.dex: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

532.name: Timburr
532.dex: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

533.name: Gurdurr
533.dex: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

534.name: Conkeldurr
534.dex: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

535.name: Tympole
535.dex: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

536.name: Palpitoad
536.dex: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

537.name: Seismitoad
537.dex: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

538.name: Throh
538.dex: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

539.name: Sawk
539.dex: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

540.name: Sewaddle
540.dex: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

541.name: Swadloon
541.dex: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

542.name: Leavanny
542.dex: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

543.name: Venipede
543.dex: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

544.name: Whirlipede
544.dex: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

545.name: Scolipede
545.dex: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

546.name: Cottonee
546.dex: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

547.name: Whimsicott
547.dex: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

548.name: Petilil
548.dex: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

549.name: Lilligant
549.dex: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

550.name: Basculin
550.dex: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

551.name: Sandile
551.dex: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

552.name: Krokorok
552.dex: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

553.name: Krookodile
553.dex: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

554.name: Darumaka
554.dex: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

555.name: Darmanitan
555.dex: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

556.name: Maractus
556.dex: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

557.name: Dwebble
557.dex: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

558.name: Crustle
558.dex: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

559.name: Scraggy
559.dex: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

560.name: Scrafty
560.dex: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

561.name: Sigilyph
561.dex: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

562.name: Yamask
562.dex: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

563.name: Cofagrigus
563.dex: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

564.name: Tirtouga
564.dex: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

565.name: Carracosta
565.dex: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

566.name: Archen
566.dex: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

567.name: Archeops
567.dex: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

568.name: Trubbish
568.dex: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

569.name: Garbodor
569.dex: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

570.name: Zorua
570.dex: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

571.name: Zoroark
571.dex: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

572.name: Minccino
572.dex: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

573.name: Cinccino
573.dex: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

574.name: Gothita
574.dex: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

575.name: Gothorita
575.dex: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

576.name: Gothitelle
576.dex: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

577.name: Solosis
577.dex: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

578.name: Duosion
578.dex: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

579.name: Reuniclus
579.dex: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

580.name: Ducklett
580.dex: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

581.name: Swanna
581.dex: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

582.name: Vanillite
582.dex: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

583.name: Vanillish
583.dex: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

584.name: Vanilluxe
584.dex: If both heads get angry simultaneously, this Pokémon expels a blizzard, burying everything in snow.

585.name: Deerling
585.dex: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

586.name: Sawsbuck
586.dex: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

587.name: Emolga
587.dex: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

588.name: Karrablast
588.dex: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

589.name: Escavalier
589.dex: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

590.name: Foongus
590.dex: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

591.name: Amoonguss
591.dex: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

592.name: Frillish
592.dex: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

593.name: Jellicent
593.dex: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

594.name: Alomomola
594.dex: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

595.name: Joltik
595.dex: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

596.name: Galvantula
596.dex: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

597.name: Ferroseed
597.dex: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

598.name: Ferrothorn
598.dex: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

599.name: Klink
599.dex: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

600.name: Klang
600.dex: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

601.name: Klinklang
601.dex: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

602.name: Tynamo
602.dex: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

603.name: Eelektrik
603.dex: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

604.name: Eelektross
604.dex: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

605.name: Elgyem
605.dex: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

606.name: Beheeyem
606.dex: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

607.name: Litwick
607.dex: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

608.name: Lampent
608.dex: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

609.name: Chandelure
609.dex: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

610.name: Axew
610.dex: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

611.name: Fraxure
611.dex: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

612.name: Haxorus
612.dex: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

613.name: Cubchoo
613.dex: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

614.name: Beartic
614.dex: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

615.name: Cryogonal
615.dex: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

616.name: Shelmet
616.dex: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

617.name: Accelgor
617.dex: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

618.name: Stunfisk
618.dex: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

619.name: Mienfoo
619.dex: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

620.name: Mienshao
620.dex: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

621.name: Druddigon
621.dex: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

622.name: Golett
622.dex: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

623.name: Golurk
623.dex: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

624.name: Pawniard
624.dex: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

625.name: Bisharp
625.dex: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

626.name: Bouffalant
626.dex: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

627.name: Rufflet
627.dex: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

628.name: Braviary
628.dex: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

629.name: Vullaby
629.dex: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

630.name: Mandibuzz
630.dex: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

631.name: Heatmor
631.dex: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

632.name: Durant
632.dex: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

633.name: Deino
633.dex: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

634.name: Zweilous
634.dex: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

635.name: Hydreigon
635.dex: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

636.name: Larvesta
636.dex: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

637.name: Volcarona
637.dex: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

638.name: Cobalion
638.dex: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

639.name: Terrakion
639.dex: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

640.name: Virizion
640.dex: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

641.name: Tornadus
641.dex: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

642.name: Thundurus
642.dex: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

643.name: Reshiram
643.dex: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

644.name: Zekrom
644.dex: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

645.name: Landorus
645.dex: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

646.name: Kyurem
646.dex: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

647.name: Keldeo
647.dex: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

648.name: Meloetta
648.dex: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

649.name: Genesect
649.dex: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

650.name: Chespin
650.dex: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

651.name: Quilladin
651.dex: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

652.name: Chesnaught
652.dex: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

653.name: Fennekin
653.dex: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

654.name: Braixen
654.dex: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

655.name: Delphox
655.dex: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

656.name: Froakie
656.dex: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

657.name: Frogadier
657.dex: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

658.name: Greninja
658.dex: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

659.name: Bunnelby
659.dex: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

660.name: Diggersby
660.dex: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

661.name: Fletchling
661.dex: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

662.name: Fletchinder
662.dex: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

663.name: Talonflame
663.dex: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

664.name: Scatterbug
664.dex: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

665.name: Spewpa
665.dex: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

666.name: Vivillon
666.dex: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

667.name: Litleo
667.dex: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

668.name: Pyroar
668.dex: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.

669.name: Flab b
669.dex: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

670.name: Floette
670.dex: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

671.name: Florges
671.dex: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

672.name: Skiddo
672.dex: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

673.name: Gogoat
673.dex: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

674.name: Pancham
674.dex: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

675.name: Pangoro
675.dex: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

676.name: Furfrou
676.dex: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

677.name: Espurr
677.dex: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

678.name: Meowstic
678.dex: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

679.name: Honedge
679.dex: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

680.name: Doublade
680.dex: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

681.name: Aegislash
681.dex: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

682.name: Spritzee
682.dex: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

683.name: Aromatisse
683.dex: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

684.name: Swirlix
684.dex: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

685.name: Slurpuff
685.dex: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

686.name: Inkay
686.dex: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

687.name: Malamar
687.dex: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

688.name: Binacle
688.dex: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

689.name: Barbaracle
689.dex: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

690.name: Skrelp
690.dex: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

691.name: Dragalge
691.dex: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

692.name: Clauncher
692.dex: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

693.name: Clawitzer
693.dex: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

694.name: Helioptile
694.dex: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

695.name: Heliolisk
695.dex: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

696.name: Tyrunt
696.dex: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.

697.name: Tyrantrum
697.dex: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.

698.name: Amaura
698.dex: This calm Pokémon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.

699.name: Aurorus
699.dex: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.

700.name: Sylveon
700.dex: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.

701.name: Hawlucha
701.dex: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

702.name: Dedenne
702.dex: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

703.name: Carbink
703.dex: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

704.name: Goomy
704.dex: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.

705.name: Sliggoo
705.dex: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.

706.name: Goodra
706.dex: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.

707.name: Klefki
707.dex: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

708.name: Phantump
708.dex: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

709.name: Trevenant
709.dex: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

710.name: Pumpkaboo
710.dex: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

711.name: Gourgeist
711.dex: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

712.name: Bergmite
712.dex: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

713.name: Avalugg
713.dex: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

714.name: Noibat
714.dex: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

715.name: Noivern
715.dex: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

716.name: Xerneas
716.dex: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

717.name: Yveltal
717.dex: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

718.name: Zygarde
718.dex: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.
